article.headline: IUPUI 84, Ind.-South Bend 59
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Alex Young scored 16 points and Jon Avery added 15 as IUPUI beat Indiana-South Bend 84-59 on Tuesday night. The Jaguars (5-2) led only 14-10 but broke the game open with an 11-0 run midway through the first half. Young had six points during that streak, and IUPUI stretched the lead to 45-20 at halftime and coasted the rest of the way. Robert Glenn added 14 points and 11 rebounds and Gary Patterson finished with 11 points for IUPUI. South Bend (3-7) was led by Quintin Brooks, who hit 6-of-7 3-pointers and finished with 24 points. Ben Werner and Mark Comparato added 11 points each.
